openvpn
# VPN_SWITCH_BINARY_openvpn - OpenVPN process binary
#
# Used to identify running OpenVPN processes and to execute OpenVPN commands.
# This follows the VPN_SWITCH_BINARY_<protocol> naming convention for
# protocol-agnostic binary lookup.
#
# Default: openvpn (expects binary in PATH)
# FreeBSD typical location: /usr/local/sbin/openvpn
#
# Used by:
#   - check_and_create_session(): Detect running VPN processes
#   - _openvpn_connect1(): Execute OpenVPN connection
#   - _openvpn_disconnect1(): Execute OpenVPN disconnection
